text.tspan: Medical doctors per 1,000 people vs. GDP per capita, 2019
Medical doctors include generalist physicians and specialist medical practitioners.
GDP per capita is measured in constant international-$. This means it is adjusted for price differences between
countries and adjusted for inflation to allow comparisons between countries and over time.
Data source: Data compiled from multiple sources by World Bank
